      "colorPalette": "# Lapis for the Sky, Gold for the Altar\n\nThe palette draws on an Italian cathedral: fresco-blue vaults, gilded altarpieces, and warm travertine marble.\n\n## Lapis Fresco Blue\n- **Header / chrome:** `#1E3A5F` — deep fresco blue, the sacred ground.\n- **Rail & card surface:** `#2C4E7A` — lighter fresco for depth.\n\n## Basilica Gold\n- **Accents & hairlines:** `#C9A227` — gold leaf; deepen to `#9C7A2E`.\n\n## Travertine\n- **Working surfaces:** warm ivory `#FAF6EC` / `#FFFDF8` so charts stay readable.",
      "contentVoice": null,
      "inspirations": [
        "Giotto & Fra Angelico fresco blues",
        "Basilica gold-leaf mosaics",
        "Florentine & Sienese marble inlay",
        "Renaissance wedding-invitation engraving",
        "Latin-cross and rose-window geometry"
      ],
      "designMindset": "# Reverence Without Clutter\n\nA cathedral is grand, but a seating tool must stay legible. Concentrate the saturated lapis blue in the chrome (header, rails); keep every working surface on warm travertine so the room chart and roster remain scannable. Gold is a hairline and an accent, never a fill.",
